2. Chip Architecture

2.1 Three-Layer Physical Mechanism

Transmission Layer: Photon waveguides + frictionless liquid-state tracks
· Heat elimination: No electron-lattice collisions; Q = I²Rt ≡ 0
· Key parameters: n=1.4; v=2.14x10^8 m/s

Switching Layer: Micro-ring resonator refractive index modulation
· Heat elimination: No substantial current; refractive field adjustment only
· Key parameters: Switching energy near zero

Structural Layer: 0.5nm logic islands + liquid microfluidic buffer zones
· Heat elimination: Residual heat instantly absorbed by liquid medium
· Key parameters: Liquid layer 10um thick

2.2 Liquid Waveguide Propagation Delay Analysis

Propagation speed: v = c/n = 3x10^8 / 1.4 = 2.14x10^8 m/s

Medium comparison:
· Silicon waveguide: n=3.5, v=0.86x10^8 m/s, 100um delay ~1.16ns (FAILS)
· Liquid waveguide: n=1.4, v=2.14x10^8 m/s, 100um delay ~0.47ns (PASS)

Timing slack: slack = 2ns - 0.5ns(propagation) - 1ns(setup) = 0.5ns > 0 PASS

2.3 Four Functional Islands Layout

CPU:      50,000 gates  Center (220, 250)um  Radius 55um
MEM:      30,000 gates  Center (600, 250)um  Radius 43um
GPU:      80,000 gates  Center (220, 600)um  Radius 70um
BUS:      20,000 gates  Center (600, 600)um  Radius 35um
ENG CORE: Energy pool   Center (500, 500)um  Radius 60um

Resonance trigger: all 4 islands online + res_lock=1 + normal temp -> 32 cycles -> resonance=1
Resonance effect: 500MHz equivalent clock, EFF=98.04%, OPS from 20K to 88K+

Chip area: 1000um x 1000um = 1mm²  Total gates: 180,000

